**7\. Role-based access model**

The app determines admin vs member status on the server in src/lib/server-auth.ts.

The logic is:

- verify Firebase ID token using Admin SDK
- read roles_admin/{uid}
- if document exists, user is admin
- otherwise user is member

**This means you must create:**

- a roles_admin collection
- one document per admin user
- document ID must equal the Firebase Auth UID

**Example**

roles_admin/  
abc123uid/  
email: <admin@yourdomain.com>  
createdAt: 2026-03-14T00:00:00.000Z  
createdBy: seed-script

**Why this matters**

Without roles_admin, every authenticated user is treated as a member. Which is safer than the reverse, at least. Small mercies.

